The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Oct. 3 (PTI): The IAF will buy a search and rescue system for post-crash recovery of crew, aircraft and helicopters with air mishaps dogging its fleet.           
	The system being bought will be put to use by the IAF for over 20 years, an IAF officer said. On an average, the IAF suffers about 10 air crashes a year. This year, it has reported over half-a-dozen mishaps.                   
	 Kathmandu (PTI): Five Indians possessing arms have been arrested with 12 Nepalis for allegedly helping examinees who were appearing for an MBBS entrance examination at a college in Kathmandu. The Nepalis were released after they were found innocent.                  
	 Ghaziabad (PTI): A woman, lodged in a flood relief camp, allegedly committed suicide on Saturday after she returned to her village and found her house had been ruined, police said. Rita, 30, allegedly consumed poison at Garhmukteshwar in Ghaziabad.                  
	 Kanpur (PTI): A Thakur-dominated village in Uttar Pradesh that did not receive a single nomination for five years for the gram pradhan post after being declared a reserve seat, has been declared general. The Dalits were too scared to come forward to fight elections, sources said.                  
	 Nagpur (PTI): A group of suspected Maoists killed a middle-aged woman and a village revenue official in Maharashtras Gadchiroli district, police said. The Maoists allegedly killed both Mayabai Sukhdeo Duga, 40, and Murlidhar Mahadore, 50, by slitting their throats.                  
	 Jaipur (PTI): Indias first three-deck elevated track, costing around Rs 200 crore, will be constructed with a Metro line on top to ease traffic congestion on Ajmer Road in Jaipur, officials said. A total 2.95km elevated track, which will include a four-lane 1.6km double-decker road will be constructed from Gopalpura Badi to Sushilpura on Ajmer Road, they said.                                                                                                                                              
